  "original_title": "\u0db8\u0dc4\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca\u0daf, \u0db6\u0dd0\u0dc3\u0dd2\u0dbd\u0dca \u0dc4\u0dd9\u0da7 \u0dc0\u0dd9\u0db1\u0d9a\u0db8\u0dca \u0dbb\u0da7 \u0dba\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1\u0dda \u0db1\u0dd0\u0dad\u0dd2\u0dbd\u0dd4",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Mahinda and Basil will not leave the country until tomorrow",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Former Prime Minister Mahinda Rajapaksa and former Finance Minister Basil Rajapaksa informed the Supreme Court yesterday through their lawyers that they will not travel abroad until tomorrow (14th) and former Central Bank Governor Ajit Nivard Cabral will not travel abroad without the permission of the court.",
        "Former Finance Ministers Mahinda Rajapaksa, Basil Rajapaksa and former Central Bank Governors Ajith Nivard Cabral and Professor W. D. This was informed when the petition submitted by Lakshman and others requesting to ban foreign travel was called through a motion.",
        "A fundamental rights petition filed by a group including Chandra Jayaratne, a former president of the Chamber of Commerce, Julian Bowling Jehan Kanagaratne, a swimming champion, and Transparency International Sri Lanka Institute was summoned yesterday through a motion to order an investigation against the people responsible for the current economic crisis.",
        "The motion related to these petitions was called before a bench of five judges including Supreme Court Justices Yasanta Kodagoda Buwaneka Aluvihare Aluvihare.",
        "The citizens of the country know the position of the President of the People's Government of Sri Lanka among the persons responsible for the facts mentioned in these fundamental rights petitions that have been submitted requesting that an investigation be ordered against the people responsible for the economic crisis that Sri Lanka is currently facing. The court was informed that an impossible situation has been created.",
        "Based on this situation, the petitioners, stating that information has been revealed that the rest of the respondents in this case are ready to flee the country, have requested through the motion to issue an order to prevent them from traveling abroad without the permission of the court.",
        "When these petitions were called, the lawyers representing Mr. Mahinda Rajapaksa and Mr. Basil Rajapaksa presented the facts and informed that their clients are not ready to leave the country until tomorrow.",
        "The lawyers representing former central bank governor Mr. Ajith Nivard Cabral presented the facts and informed that their client has no need to leave the country and if he is going to leave the country, he will take the permission of the court to leave the country.",
        "As no lawyer appeared for the former Secretary of the Ministry of Finance Mr. SR Artigala, an order was issued prohibiting him from leaving the country until the 14th.",
        "After considering the facts presented, the Supreme Court ordered these petitions to be called on the 27th."
      ],
